## Release Flow

1. Make commits following the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format
2. Run `make release` locally â€” this bumps the version via commitizen, pushes commits and tags
3. The tag push triggers CI: **checks** â†’ **tests** â†’ **release** + **deploy-docs**{% if publish_to_pypi %} + **publish-package**{% endif %}
4. Preview first with `make release -- --dry-run`
